  "prompt": "I want to activate my old whatsapp but I'm over seas and have the old number?",
  "response": "Activating your old WhatsApp number while overseas can be a bit tricky, but it's possible with a few steps. Here\u2019s what you can do:\n\n1. **Access to the Old Number**: Ensure you have access to your old phone number, as WhatsApp will need to send a verification code to that number. If you have roaming enabled on your old SIM card, you should be able to receive the SMS or call with the verification code.\n\n2. **Install WhatsApp**: If you haven\u2019t already, download and install WhatsApp on your device.\n\n3. **Verification Process**: Open WhatsApp and enter your old phone number. Wait for the verification code to be sent via SMS or call. \n\n4. **Receive the Code**: If your old SIM card is in a device that can receive SMS or calls, you should be able to get the verification code. Enter that code in WhatsApp.\n\n5. **Alternative Methods**: If you cannot receive the SMS, you might have the option to receive the verification code via a phone call. Make sure you are in an area where international calls can be received.\n\n6. **Contact Support**: If you face issues with the verification process, you can contact WhatsApp support for further assistance.\n\nIf you no longer have access to your old number, consider contacting your old mobile provider to see if they can assist in reactivating the number or providing a temporary solution to receive the verification code.\n\nRemember to check for any roaming charges or international fees that may apply when using your old SIM card overseas.",
